net.sourceforge.fastupload

Class ContentHeaderMap

  • java.lang.Object
    • java.util.AbstractMap<K,V>
      • java.util.HashMap<String,String>
        • net.sourceforge.fastupload.ContentHeaderMap
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Serializable, Cloneable, Map<String,String>

    public class ContentHeaderMap
extends HashMap<String,String>
    Represent headers of a boundary of multipart/form-data input stream. refer to RFC1867ï¼Œ Every boundary has it owner header. for example,
    ----------------------------------------------------------------------------- 
     --AaB03x
    content-disposition: form-data; name="pics"; filename="file1.txt"
    Content-Type: text/plain
    ----------------------------------------------------------------------------

    The header contains key information for form-based uploading file. The class use Map structure stores this information and provide some convenience methods to fetch this information from the map.

    Author:
    Link Qian
